events.name: Next â€™19 Extended San Jose & Hands-on Coding on GCP
events.description:
A brief introduction about Next Extended: This is an event to share the AI/ML related events at Google Next 19 in San Francisco last month. This will be followed with Code Jams where participants are expected to participate, with hands on.

Presenters will share slides and each participant will get access to Qwiklabs platform to learn and try out the AI/ML tools in the the Google Clould Platform.

Requirements from the participants:
1) Laptop with Chrome and Wifi
2) Gmail account to access google files
3) Familiarity with Google Cloud Platform (https://cloud.google.com/docs/overview/), we will give an intro session.

What to expect:
1) Access to Qwiklabs and one month free coupon. (https://go.qwiklabs.com/next-19-extended)
2) Code Jam (handson programming experience) in solving an AI/ML problem.
3) Opportunity to pair program.

Lunch will be provided.

events.name: Fireside chat with Andrew Ng & Laurence Moroney
events.description:
This event is cross-posted from Eventbrite.

Join us for a fireside chat with Andrew Ng and Laurence Moroney to celebrate the launch of the deeplearning.ai TensorFlow Specialization. Andrew and Laurence will discuss exciting AI trends, tips, and tricks for TensorFlow, and how to build a career in AI. They'll also be taking questions from the audience.

Register at: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/deeplearningai-pie-ai-google-tickets-64629179616

You MUST be registered for this event on Eventbrite to attend. The organizers are not able to admit non-ticket holders into the building due to limited capacity. You will be required to sign in with a valid ID at the entrance.

events.name: GDG Cloud DevFest with Hands-on Coding on GCP
events.description:
Join us! Learn to program in Data Science and Machine Learning on Google Cloud Platform and hear from women with successful careers in Data Science.

Agenda:

* Introduction to Machine Learning: Get an overview of Machine Learning
* Round table - Women in Data Science
* Lunch (Will be provided!)
* Hands-on Code Jam - complete quests to earn one-month free Qwiklabs access and one-month free Coursera access coupon! Do more quests and get one more free month of Qwiklabs.
* Win Prizes!

Requirements from the participants:
1) Laptop with Chrome and Wifi
2) Gmail account to access google files
3) Familiarity with Google Cloud Platform (https://cloud.google.com/docs/overview/), we will give an intro session.

What to expect:
1) Access to Qwiklabs and one month free coupon.
2) Code Jam (hands-on programming experience) in solving an AI/ML problem.
3) Opportunity to pair program.

Lunch will be provided.

events.name: {Free - Online} Hands On : Intro to BigQuery on GCP [ 3 hours]
events.description:
Link for the event: https://hangouts.google.com/call/T_ufSGIhsb2U4gHJ1aR6AEEE

The online course introduces to BigQuery on Google Cloud.
About this Event

This online hands-on class introduces a series that helps you to learn about ML/AL on Google Cloud starting with BigQuery
The series consists of the following parts

- Query a public dataset
- Create a custom table
- Load data into a table
- Query a table

Prerequisites:

- Knowledge of databases
- Have a demo account on Google Cloud Platform https://console.cloud.google.com/freetrial
- Working knowledge of Python.

Requirements:

- Laptop with Chrome or Chromebook
